Package use_cases.add_edit_expenses_use_case

Class ExpenseID

  • java.lang.Object
    • use_cases.add_edit_expenses_use_case.ExpenseInputData
  • public class ExpenseID
extends java.lang.Object
    ExpenseID contains all user inputs. Created in ExpenseC and used in ExpenseUCI to perform addExpenseInMonth() and editExpenseInMonth().

      • ExpenseID

        public ExpenseID​(java.lang.String name,
                 java.lang.Object value,
                 java.lang.String oldCategory,
                 boolean isRecurringExpense,
                 int monthID,
                 SessionStorage session,
                 java.lang.String oldExpense)
        Constructs ExpenseID for adding/editing an existing Expense Object.
        Parameters:
        name - Expense name
        value - Expense budget
        oldCategory - String Category name representing an existing Category in which the Expense belongs to.
        isRecurringExpense - boolean indicating whether an Expense is recurring.
        monthID - An int representing the month which the Expense Object belongs to.
        session - The current session which the MonthlyStorage Object belongs to.
        oldExpense - String Expense name representing an existing Expense in the MonthlyStorage Object the user wish to edit.
